    <p>Emma Onraet is a post-doctoral researcher at the Department of Developmental, Personality and Social Psychology of Ghent University. In 2012 she obtained her PhD about the role of cognitive style, threat, and well-being in right-wing ideological attitudes. As a post-doctoral researcher, Emma first worked on cognitive and emotional abilities in relationship with right-wing ideology and racial prejudice. Her current research interest are the effects of ethnic diversity on trust and intergroup relations, and the role of intergroup contact and threat.</p>
